text.__SUMMARY__: Cyperus aquatilis is a sedge of the family Cyperaceae that is native to Australia.The annual sedge typically grows to a height of 3.5 to 5 centimetres (1.4 to 2.0 in). The plant blooms between April and August producing green-brown flowers.In Western Australia it is found around creeks and swamps in the Kimberley region where it grows in sandy-loamy soils often around laterite.
